{
  "doc_id": "39308",
  "text": "Generally, in hemorrhagic shock there is a significant decrease in microvascular oxygenation, which is highly correlated with macrocirculatory indexes such as cardiac index and mean arterial pressure [CITATION_1] . Post-operative bleeding leads to hemodynamic instability, which might result in ischemic injury to the bile duct. Simultaneously, bile duct cells are vulnerable to ischemia reperfusion injury [CITATION_2] . Thus, it is reasonable to believe that post-operative bleeding leads to development of BCs. To prevent BCs, it is vitally important to keep vital signs stable following liver transplantation.",
